    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Common term for several poplar trees that are typically native to cold regions with cool summers, in the north of the Northern Hemisphere  but extending south at high altitudes in the mountains.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
